01:44:42.800 --> 01:44:48.318
..l want you to invade the offices,
which are over there in the corner,...

01:44:48.400 --> 01:44:51.756
..through that door,
and as far as you can, loot them.

01:44:51.840 --> 01:44:53.990
(whistling, applause)

01:44:56.480 --> 01:44:59.916
Office equipment, computers,
musical equipment,...

01:45:00.000 --> 01:45:02.878
..take it all, use it wisely,...

01:45:02.960 --> 01:45:05.918
..let a thousand Mancunians bloom.

01:45:06.000 --> 01:45:07.956
Good night, God bless.

01:45:08.040 --> 01:45:09.996
(cheering)

01:45:13.440 --> 01:45:15.396
(music resumes)

01:45:28.360 --> 01:45:30.316
(sighs)

01:45:30.840 --> 01:45:32.592
Morning.

01:45:33.040 --> 01:45:35.270
All right, Tone,
how you doing, mate?

01:45:35.360 --> 01:45:37.555
- Good, very good.
- Great, T.

01:45:37.640 --> 01:45:40.313
l'm really sorry about what happened,
d'you know what l mean?

01:45:40.400 --> 01:45:43.198
- lt just fuckin'...
- Don't worry about it, mate.

01:45:44.640 --> 01:45:46.596
lt's just... you know...

01:45:54.240 --> 01:45:57.789
This is fuckin' great, this is.
This is brilliant stuff.

01:45:57.880 --> 01:46:00.997
Yeah, Shaun brought it back
from Barbados.

01:46:01.120 --> 01:46:03.759
- Well done, Shaun.
- Don't mention it.

01:46:03.840 --> 01:46:06.434
So it wasn't a complete waste of time?

01:46:06.520 --> 01:46:09.751
No, l had a great time, what l can
remember. Know what l mean?

01:46:20.360 --> 01:46:22.316
(whooshing)

01:46:24.680 --> 01:46:27.148
(Tony's voice)
Tony, you did a good job.

01:46:27.240 --> 01:46:29.276
Basically, you were right:

01:46:29.360 --> 01:46:31.715
..Shaun is the greatest poet
since Yeats.

01:46:31.800 --> 01:46:34.792
This is amazing.
Can l have it in writing?

01:46:34.880 --> 01:46:38.953
lt is already written in the sinews
of history and the hearts of men.

01:46:39.040 --> 01:46:41.429
lt's a pity you didn't sign
the Smiths...

01:46:41.520 --> 01:46:43.476
..but you were right about
Mick Hucknall.

01:46:43.560 --> 01:46:45.516
His music's rubbish
and he's a ginger.

01:46:46.360 --> 01:46:48.316
Vini Reilly, by the way,...

01:46:48.400 --> 01:46:50.356
..is way overdue a revival.

01:46:50.440 --> 01:46:52.510
You might think about
a greatest hits.

01:46:52.600 --> 01:46:54.795
lt's a good idea.

01:46:54.880 --> 01:46:57.553
lt's good music to chill out to.

01:46:58.000 --> 01:46:59.991
Yeah, you're right.

01:47:00.080 --> 01:47:02.116
l usually am.

01:47:04.720 --> 01:47:06.676
(whooshing)

01:47:06.760 --> 01:47:09.399
Are you all right, there, Tony?

01:47:10.160 --> 01:47:12.116
Yeah, l've just seen God.

01:47:12.200 --> 01:47:14.430
- You did what?
- l've just seen God.

01:47:14.520 --> 01:47:16.476
- Did you?
- Yeah.

01:47:16.560 --> 01:47:18.516
What did he look like?

01:47:18.760 --> 01:47:20.716
He looked like me.

01:47:21.520 --> 01:47:23.476
How d'you mean?

01:47:23.560 --> 01:47:25.516
He was the double of me.

01:47:28.400 --> 01:47:30.356
lt's written in the Bible, isn't it?

01:47:30.680 --> 01:47:32.910
God made man in his own image.

01:47:34.120 --> 01:47:36.270
Yeah, but not a specific man.

01:47:38.000 --> 01:47:39.956
No, but...

01:47:40.320 --> 01:47:43.437
